===Etymology 1===
{{etyl|ang|en}} {{term|twigge|lang=ang}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{recons|twīgan|lang=gem-pro}} (compare West Frisian {{term|twiich|lang=fy}}, {{etyl|nl|-}} {{term|twijg|lang=nl}}, {{etyl|de|-}} {{term|Zweig|lang=de}}), from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{recons|dwigha|lang=ine-pro}} (compare {{etyl|cu|-}} {{term|dvigŭ|lang=cu}} 'branch', {{etyl|sq|-}} {{term|degë|lang=sq}} 'id.'), from *''dwó'' 'two'. More at [[two]].

====Pronunciation====
* {{rhymes|ɪɡ}}

====Noun====
{{slim-wikipedia}}
{{en-noun}}

# A small thin [[branch]] of a [[tree]] or [[bush]].
#: ''They used '''twigs''' and leaves as a base to start the fire.''
