|title=The Dust of Conflict
|chapter=1|url=http://openlibrary.org/works/OL4429277W
|passage=A beech wood with silver firs in it rolled down the face of the hill, and the maze of leafless '''twigs''' and dusky spires cut sharp against the soft blueness of the evening sky.}}

